OL,3,CForce fined #60,000 after officers
OL,4,Cinjured by petrol bombs
OL,6,FAfter the hearing HSE inspector
OL,7,FJennifer Elsegood, said: "Being a
OL,8,Fserving police officer is a job that
OL,9,Fcarries with it levels of risk,
OL,10,Fhowever while preparing officers for
OL,11,Fdangerous situations is important, it
OL,12,Fmust never come at the expense of
OL,13,Ftheir safety."
OL,15,FThe court heard 13 officers wearing
OL,16,Fflame-retardant personal protective
OL,17,Fequipment (PPE) had petrol bombs
OL,18,Fthrown at them by colleagues as part
OL,19,Fof the drill in February 2021.
